Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: An Enormous Power
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00h1brn
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 3 Dec 1986
Serving Judge Lord McCluskey gives his fifth Reith lecture from the series entitled 'Law, Justice and Democracy'. In this lecture entitled 'An Enormous Power', Lord McCluskey debates the essential constitutional difference between the British and American higher judicial systems. Debating the merits and flaws of both systems, Lord McCluskey argues against the enactment of a Bill of Rights in the United Kingdom. Show less